  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2021-10-07",
    "date": "2021-11-23T21:01:30Z",
    "text": "FDA Modernization Act of 2021\n\nThis bill allows an applicant for market approval for a new drug to use methods other than animal testing to establish the drug's safety and effectiveness. Under this bill, these alternative methods may include cell-based assays, organ chips and microphysiological systems, computer modeling, and other human biology-based test methods."
